# Testing Instructions for Claude Code

## ⚠️ MANDATORY: Run Tests After Code Changes

If you modify any firmware code (`.c` or `.h` files in the project root), you **MUST** run the test suite before completing your task.

### Quick Command (Recommended)
```bash
./test/run_tests.sh
```

### Alternative (Manual)
```bash
cmake --build test/build && test/build/test_speed
```

### Expected Output (All Tests Pass)
```
27 Tests 0 Failures 0 Ignored
OK
```

### What to Do If Tests Fail
1. Read the failure message carefully
2. Fix the bug in your code, OR
3. Update the test if behavior change was intentional
4. Never commit failing tests

